choices.text:
Sally has 3 brothers. Her brothers have 2 sisters. How many sisters does Sally have?
If Sally has 3 brothers, then her sibling structure can be represented as follows:
```
   Sally
    |
Brothers (3)
    |
Sisters (x)
```
Since the brothers have 2 sisters each, we can add that to the total number of sisters:
```
   Sally
    |
Brothers (3)
    |       Brothers (3)
     Sisters (2*2 = x + 6)
    |                      |
Sisters (x)            Brothers (1)
```
Therefore, Sally has a total of 7 sisters.
